&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Backend Engineer – Python&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Location: Indore, India&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; As a Senior Backend Engineer at Trivelta, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, and operating core backend services for our online sportsbook and casino platforms. Your work will ensure transaction integrity, player account management, and compliance with regulatory reporting, operating within high-availability environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop scalable, secure RESTful and event-driven services in Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build backend systems supporting sportsbook, casino, wallet, and player lifecycle modules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data consistency, idempotency, and transactional integrity across services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to architectural decisions aligned with scalability and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement backend logic supporting AML, KYC, responsible gaming, and jurisdictional restrictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop systems supporting audit trails, activity logging, and regulatory reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate geolocation and access-control mechanisms to meet licensing conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure adherence to data protection and privacy standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize backend performance for high-concurrency transaction environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement secure coding practices and vulnerability mitigation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to monitoring, logging, and incident response processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support business continuity and disaster recovery planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain data pipelines for fraud detection, analytics, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate with payment gateways, game providers, identity verification, and external compliance services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure secure API communication with internal and third-party systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review code and enforce engineering standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior engineers and guide design discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product, compliance, risk, and DevOps teams to translate regulatory requirements into technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of backend development experience in production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in Python for backend services and data processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building secure, scalable APIs in high-transaction systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of database design, concurrency, and system reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CI/CD workflows and production deployment practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to regulated industries such as fintech, payments, or iGaming is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of AML, KYC, audit logging, or regulatory compliance frameworks is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and documentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an On-Site role based in our Indore office. Collaboration with cross-functional teams is a core part of the position. We are seeking experienced backend engineers who understand the responsibilities of building systems in regulated markets, where stability, compliance, and audit readiness are fundamental to platform success.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trivelta operates a multi-tenant gaming platform (sportsbook, casino, poker, and affiliated products) that runs across white-label client environments in AWS. We&#39;re hiring a mid-to-senior DevOps Engineer to help us scale, harden, and automate the infrastructure and delivery pipelines that keep every client environment (dev, staging, and production) deploying safely and running reliably around the clock. You&#39;ll work closely with backend, frontend, and platform teams on everything from Kubernetes and GitOps rollouts to CI/CD pipeline design and incident response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Design, build, and maintain CI/CD pipelines (Jenkins and GitHub Actions) that support frequent, multi-environment deployments across dozens of client tenants.&lt;br&gt;• Own and evolve our Kubernetes (EKS) platform, including GitOps-based delivery with&amp;nbsp;ArgoCD.&lt;br&gt;• Write and maintain Terraform modules to provision and manage AWS infrastructure (VPC,&amp;nbsp;EKS, Lambda, API Gateway, DynamoDB, RDS/PostgreSQL, SQS/SNS, Step Functions,&amp;nbsp;CloudFront, Cognito, Secrets Manager, and S3).&lt;br&gt;• Support serverless services (AWS Lambda) and event-driven architectures built on SQS,&amp;nbsp;SNS, and Kafka.&lt;br&gt;• Manage and troubleshoot AWS Amplify deployments for Next.js-based web applications.&lt;br&gt;• Build tooling and automation to reduce manual work around environment/secrets&amp;nbsp;configuration, client onboarding, and multi-account AWS management.&lt;br&gt;• Improve observability, alerting, and on-call runbooks to reduce time-to-detect and time-to-resolve for production incidents.&lt;br&gt;• Participate in an on-call rotation and lead incident response for infrastructure and&amp;nbsp;deployment issues, including root-cause analysis and postmortems.&lt;br&gt;• Partner with backend and frontend engineers to review infrastructure-related pull requests&amp;nbsp;and unblock feature delivery.&lt;br&gt;• Contribute to security and compliance practices relevant to a regulated gaming environment (secrets management, access control, audit trails).&lt;br&gt;• Mentor other engineers on infrastructure and deployment best practices (senior-level expectation).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 4+ years of experience in a DevOps, SRE, platform, or infrastructure engineering role&amp;nbsp;(mid-level); 6+ years for senior-level consideration.&lt;br&gt;• Hands-on production experience with AWS, including at minimum EKS/Kubernetes,&amp;nbsp;Lambda, IAM, VPC networking, and CloudFront.&lt;br&gt;• Strong Terraform experience, writing and maintaining reusable modules, managing state, and troubleshooting drift/locking issues.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; • Experience building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines with Jenkins (Jenkinsfile/Groovy)and/or GitHub Actions.&lt;br&gt;• Practical experience with GitOps workflows and tools such as ArgoCD.&lt;br&gt;• Comfort working with both relational (PostgreSQL) and NoSQL (DynamoDB) data stores&lt;br&gt;from an operations perspective.&lt;br&gt;• Solid understanding of networking, DNS, load balancing, and API Gateway patterns.&lt;br&gt;• Experience debu

&lt;h3&gt;About Trivelta&lt;/h3&gt;
